Summary of Estimated Quantities

The construction quantities estimated for the substructure, divided to
show the quantities included in the construction of each of the piers and pile
bents making up the complete substructure, are summarized in Table 73.

the superstructure and the area of the roadway floor for the entire bridge
are summarized in Table 74.

ESTIMATED COST OF BRIDGE AND APPROACHES

Mrllers Island—Tolchester Site

The estimated cost of the bridge and approaches is summarized in
Table 76.

“A—DPreliminary Expenses”’ and ‘“‘E—Legal, Administrative and Over-
head Costs’ are herein estimated at $50,000 and $25,000, respectively, and
are the same as estimated for the Chesapeake Bay Bridge, Sandy Point-
Kent Island Site. ‘“B—Cost of Right-of-Way’’ is herein estimated at
$10,000, which is to be compared with $5,000 estimated cost of right-of-way
for the Chesapeake Bay Bridge, Sandy Point-Kent Island Site. The
rights-of-way required for the approaches of this bridge across Hart and Mil-
